summary: I am a MSc candidate at the Master of Science in Public Policy and Human Development of Maastricht University and UNU-MERIT. I hold a B.Sc. in Philosophy and Social sciences from the University of Crete. Prior to joining Maastricht I was an Erasmus+ researcher at EOTVOS LORAND University and a field research assistant to various academic projects related to migration, poverty and international development. My research interests focus on understanding the mechanisms and long term social effects of “collective trauma” as well as how out-group biases lead to conflict and mainly civil wars with a particular focus on Greece.
